file=Engineering/nova/operational/agent/nova-config.md · h=name: nova-config\ntype: operational/agent\nstatus: template — placeholders only, no invented values. Every field traces to a skill-file line.\nassigned_agent: nova (Engineering / Mobile)\ndate_added: 2026-07-09\n · p:=Machine-readable configuration for nova, the mobile builder. The defining field is `mobile_active` — false by default, and false means nova is entirely dormant.\n · ct:Config Template=```yaml · -td:--- The dormant switch (checked before everything) ---=mobile_active: false                    # DEFAULT false. true only when the business has a mobile app.\n# false → nova dormant; all mobile triggers route to mia (web)\n · -c(:--- Charter (senior authority) ---=security_charter_path: <FILL_IN>        # nova runs no data changes (Rail 3); operator holds signing secrets\nsigning_secrets_holder: operator        # app signing keys/certs — NEVER the agent\n · -f&:--- Framework & architecture (only when mobile_active) ---=mobile_framework: <FILL_IN>             # Flutter / React Native / native — per stack-profile\nflutter_playbook_path: <FILL_IN>        # dated playbook (asset) if Flutter\nstate_approach: <FILL_IN>               # per playbook\nlocal_store: <FILL_IN>                  # on-device persistence; secure storage for sensitive\n · -v-:--- Verification ---=device_matrix: <FILL_IN>                # real devices/OS versions to test (not simulator-only)\ndevice_farm: <FILL_IN>                  # tooling, per stack-profile\ncritical_flows: <FILL_IN>               # on-device release-gate flows (shared discipline with quinn)\n · -r-:--- Release ---=stores: <FILL_IN>                       # iOS App Store / Google Play\nstaged_rollout: [1, 10, 100]            # percent stages (mobile's rollback substitute)\nkill_switch: raj.feature-flags          # server-side disable for a bad release (the real safety net)\n · -w-:--- Wiring ---=web_counterpart: mia\napi_source: raj\ndata_model: dana\n```\n · i:=1. **`mobile_active: false` (default) → nova is dormant.** No architecture, no builds, no releases; every mobile request routes to mia with a "web-only" note. Only the operator flips it true when a real app exists (tempo's pattern).\n2. No `security_charter_path` → most-restrictive; and regardless, signing secrets are operator-held and nova runs no data changes (Rail 3).\n3. `device_matrix` unset → verification uses the widest real devices available, labeled; never simulator-only as a verdict.\n4. `staged_rollout` is the rollback substitute — mobile can't be recalled; a non-staged full release is refused.\n5. `kill_switch` (raj feature flags) is the real mobile safety net; a risky release without one is a finding.\n · f:=Default state is dormant. When active, unfilled config degrades loudly; signing stays operator-held and rollout stays staged — the two non-negotiables given mobile's weak rollback.\n